    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-21T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.002/10–2150.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barbour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-21T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 21, 1950—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 21—8:36 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>901. Am informed that in recent Peking interview with Panikkar and their [<hi
                        rend="italic">three?</hi>] Scandinavian Chiefs of Mission Vice Foreign
                    Minister Chang Han-fu said he convinced US planning preventive war. Panikkar
                    agreed adding that proof lies in continued tenure Matthews as Navy
                    Secretary.</p>
                <pb facs="1010" n="990" xml:id="pg_990"/>
                <p>Source this information who claims it comes reliable sub-source said
                    Scandinavians shocked by Panikkar’s general sympathy with Chinese
                    Communists.</p>
                <p>Department pass Delhi. Repeated info Delhi 43.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barbour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
